  "body": "Hello. In my project I'm using technique similar to http://jamesknelson.com/rendering-react-components-to-the-document-body/. Here we take `this.props.children` and render them inside another React tree, connected to a `body` child node.\n\nThe problem here is that `this.props.children` or its descendants may want a context, but it is empty for the separate tree, because we use fresh `ReactDOM.render` call. Right now I'm using the function like:\n\n``` js\nexport function extractContext(component) {\n    let context = {};\n    if (component._reactInternalInstance && component._reactInternalInstance._context) {\n        let internalContext = component._reactInternalInstance._context;\n        for(let key in internalContext) {\n            if (internalContext.hasOwnProperty(key) && key[0] !== '_') {\n                context[key] = internalContext[key];\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    return context;\n}\n```\n\nTo extract context inside my popup and then I create a wrapper that takes that context and pushes it down to the new tree. Maybe there is a better way to transfer entire context into `ReactDOM.render` without the knowledge about context's internals?\n",
